Tier-2 #77 holistic diagnosis of the warm-red bench_exception_heavy (0.68×).
Confirmed #76's hypothesis: the inc_ref/dec_ref churn (~22% of cycles) and the
~70 MiB/30-iter leak share ONE root — RETENTION. Every raised-and-immediately-
caught exception accrues 3 inc_ref but only 2 dec_ref per iteration and ends at
refcount 2, never freed (at 500k raises: live_objects=500628, MOLT_ASSERT_NO_LEAK
trips). Identical on native + LLVM -> shared frontend IR ownership model.

Root cause: a function with a try/except handler is never drop-inserted
(drop_insertion.rs:450 bails on has_exception_handlers() — dominance liveness is
unsound over exception CFG), so the native value-tracking RC is the sole release
path; but the exception-producing ops (exception_new*, exception_last*) register
their OWNED results in NEITHER block_tracked_obj NOR tracked_obj_vars, so the
existing check_exception diverted-control drain never releases them. The two
leaked owned refs are the creation ref (raise arg) and the exception_last_pending
ref (handler match/bind). Full inc/dec site map + structural fix (register the
exception temps as value-tracked / re-enable drops for exception CFG — both are
round-13 files #77 is scoped out of) in the baton; batoned to #58/#19.

This commit is ADDITIVE ONLY (no behavior change, no partial fix):
- memory/project_exception_loop_leak_baton.md: complete lifecycle map, exact
  inc/dec sites, MOLT_PROFILE evidence, semantics tripwires, gates.
- tests/differential/memory/exception_raise_catch_loop_leak.py: RED leak
  regression (3 handler shapes: as-bind / no-as / from-chain), byte-identical to
  CPython, trips MOLT_ASSERT_NO_LEAK today, flips GREEN when the fix lands.
- object/mod.rs: route the MOLT_TRACE_EXC_RC diagnostic (the tool that pinned the
  rc-2 retention) through a cached OnceLock flag trace_exception_rc() like
  debug_bigint_rc, so it is a single atomic load when off — no environ-lock tax on
  the hot inc/dec path.

Gates: cargo -p molt-runtime --lib + -p molt-backend --features "llvm
native-backend" --lib both 0 fail / 0 warn. Exception differential corpus
byte-identical (the 2 fails exception_hierarchy + exception_propagation_no_exc_stack
are PRE-EXISTING at origin/main HEAD = socket-intrinsics/env, proven by
stash-isolation).

